#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:4
msgid "Control System Electronics"
msgstr "Electrónica del sistema de control"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:6
msgid ""
"This page contains a breakdown of known electronics in the REV Robotics "
"control system, as well as notes regarding them."
msgstr ""
"Esta página contiene un desglose de los componentes electrónicos conocidos "
"del sistema de control de REV Robotics, así como notas sobre ellos."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:9
msgid "Expansion Hub Internals"
msgstr "Componentes internos del Expansion Hub"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:11
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:18
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:109
msgid ""
"Don't take apart a Control or Expansion Hub unless you really know what you "
"are doing. They can be damaged in the process, especially if one does not "
"know how to properly reassemble it."
msgstr ""
"No desmonte un Centro de Control o Expansión a menos que realmente sepa lo "
"que está haciendo. Pueden resultar dañados en el proceso, especialmente si "
"no se sabe cómo volver a montarlos correctamente."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:14
msgid "Lynx Board"
msgstr "Tablero Lynx"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:16
msgid ""
"\"Lynx\" is the codename of the board within the Expansion Hub and Control "
"Hub that interacts with hardware. References to \"Lynx\" made in the FTC\\ "
"|reg| SDK refer to this board. It appears to have been developed by both REV"
" Robotics and `DEKA <https://dekaresearch.com/>`_ (Dean Kamen's company). A "
"reverse-engineered schematic can be found `here "
"<https://github.com/DuckTapeAndAPrayer/LynxSchematic>`_."
msgstr ""
"\"Lynx\" es el nombre en clave de la placa dentro del Expansion Hub y "
"Control Hub que interactúa con el hardware. Las referencias a \"Lynx\" en el"
" SDK de FTC se refieren a esta placa. Parece haber sido desarrollada tanto "
"por REV Robotics como por `DEKA <https://dekaresearch.com/>`_ (la empresa de"
" Dean Kamen). Un esquema de ingeniería inversa se puede encontrar `aquí "
"<https://github.com/DuckTapeAndAPrayer/LynxSchematic>`_."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:23
msgid "A Lynx board that was removed from its case"
msgstr "Una placa Lynx sacada de su caja"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:26
msgid "Processor"
msgstr "Procesador"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:28
msgid ""
"The microcontroller used by the Lynx board is a `Texas Instruments "
"TM4C123GH6PGE <https://www.ti.com/product/TM4C123GH6PGE>`_, with an Arm "
"Cortex-M4F processor running at 80 MHZ."
msgstr ""
"El microcontrolador utilizado por la placa Lynx es un `Texas Instruments "
"TM4C123GH6PGE <https://www.ti.com/product/TM4C123GH6PGE>`_, con un "
"procesador Arm Cortex-M4F funcionando a 80 MHZ."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:31
msgid "Ports"
msgstr "Puertos"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:33
msgid "The Lynx board has the following ports:"
msgstr "La placa Lynx tiene los siguientes puertos:"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:35
msgid "Two UART Debug Ports"
msgstr "Dos puertos de depuración UART"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:37
msgid ""
"The top port outputs a continuous high speed CSV stream of data from the "
"various subsystems in the hub."
msgstr ""
"El puerto superior emite un flujo continuo de datos CSV de alta velocidad "
"procedentes de los distintos subsistemas del hub."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:38
msgid ""
"The bottom port outputs data at a baud rate of 115200 at a user specified "
"verbosity."
msgstr ""
"El puerto inferior emite datos a una velocidad en baudios de 115200 con una "
"verbosidad especificada por el usuario."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:39
msgid "Four I2C Ports"
msgstr "Cuatro puertos I2C"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:41
msgid "These ports are 100/400 kHz compliant."
msgstr "Estos puertos son compatibles con 100/400 kHz."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:42
msgid ""
"The ports are connected to separate busses, so there is generally no need to"
" be concerned about address collisions.  However, be aware that the internal"
" IMU shares the I2C bus with I2C port 0."
msgstr ""
"Los puertos están conectados a buses separados, por lo que generalmente no "
"hay necesidad de preocuparse por colisiones de direcciones.  Sin embargo, "
"ten en cuenta que la IMU interna comparte el bus I2C con el puerto I2C 0."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:43
msgid ""
"There appear to be integrated pull up resistors on this port (potentially "
"using the built-in configurable pull-up/pull-down resistors integrated into "
"the MCU)."
msgstr ""
"Parece que hay resistencias pull up integradas en este puerto "
"(potencialmente utilizando las resistencias pull-up/pull-down configurables "
"integradas en la MCU)."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:44
msgid "Eight DIO Ports"
msgstr "Ocho puertos DIO"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:46
msgid ""
"3.3V only, current limited, can briefly supply more than the rated current "
"spec. Pulled up internally."
msgstr ""
"Sólo 3,3 V, corriente limitada, puede suministrar brevemente más corriente "
"que la especificada. Tirado hacia arriba internamente."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:47
msgid "Four Analog Ports"
msgstr "Cuatro puertos analógicos"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:49
msgid ""
"These ports are 5V compliant; you can use a level shifter to supply 5v to "
"the sensor, but take care the analog line bypasses the level shifter. The "
"VIN and GND lines, however, must pass through the level shifter for it to "
"work."
msgstr ""
"Estos puertos son compatibles con 5V; puedes utilizar un variador de nivel "
"para suministrar 5v al sensor, pero ten cuidado de que la línea analógica no"
" pase por el variador de nivel. Las líneas VIN y GND, sin embargo, deben "
"pasar a través del variador de nivel para que funcione."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:50
msgid "Six Servo Ports"
msgstr "Seis servopuertos"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:52
msgid ""
"The 5V supply on the servo ports is default OFF, and will only enable once a"
" servo is used. All six 5V pins are switched on and off together, and "
"disabling PWM on one port will switch all of the ports off unless another "
"servo is used."
msgstr ""
"El suministro de 5V en los puertos de servo está apagado por defecto, y sólo"
" se activará una vez que se utilice un servo. Los seis pines de 5V se "
"activan y desactivan juntos, y desactivar PWM en un puerto desactivará todos"
" los puertos a menos que se utilice otro servo."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:53
msgid ""
"Each pair of 2 side-by-side ports is rated for a maximum current draw of 2 "
"amps, and the combined set of servo + 5V ports is rated for a maximum total "
"current draw of 5 amps."
msgstr ""
"Cada par de 2 puertos uno al lado del otro está clasificado para un consumo "
"máximo de corriente de 2 amperios, y el conjunto combinado de puertos servo "
"+ 5V está clasificado para un consumo máximo total de corriente de 5 "
"amperios."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:54
msgid "Two 5V Power Ports"
msgstr "Dos puertos de alimentación de 5 V"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:56
msgid ""
"The pair of 5V supply ports in rated for a maximum current draw of 2 amps, "
"and shares the total 5 amp limit with the servo ports."
msgstr ""
"El par de puertos de alimentación de 5 V tiene un consumo máximo de "
"corriente de 2 amperios y comparte el límite total de 5 amperios con los "
"puertos de servo."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:57
msgid "Four Motor Ports"
msgstr "Cuatro puertos de motor"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:59
msgid ""
"The motor driver is a ST Microelectronics VNH5050 motor driver IC, which is "
"capabile of handling well over the maximum amount of current an FTC motor "
"can draw. It has integrated current sensing, and built-in thermal and "
"current safety limits."
msgstr ""
"El controlador del motor es un circuito integrado ST Microelectronics "
"VNH5050, capaz de manejar una corriente muy superior a la máxima que puede "
"consumir un motor FTC. Dispone de detección de corriente integrada y límites"
" de seguridad térmicos y de corriente incorporados."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:60
msgid ""
"The output does not brake the H-bridge during the PWM off cycle. What this "
"means is that there might be linearity issues while deaccelerating, because "
"of momentum in the motor."
msgstr ""
"La salida no frena el puente H durante el ciclo de apagado del PWM. Esto "
"significa que puede haber problemas de linealidad al desacelerar, debido al "
"impulso del motor."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:61
msgid "Four Encoder Ports"
msgstr "Cuatro puertos de codificador"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:63
msgid ""
"**IMPORTANT: Only two of the encoder ports (Ports 0 and 3) can accurately "
"track position/velocity at high speeds**. There are two methods of "
"connecting an encoder internally to the Texas Instruments microprocessor, "
"through the Quadrature Encoder Interface (QEI) and through General-Purpose "
"Timers (GPTs). Ports 0 and 3 use the integrated QEI and are extremely "
"accurate at high speeds, whereas encoders using the GPTs often start to "
"loose counts at high speeds. As a result, high Count per Revolution (CPR) "
"encoders (those with more than around 4000 counts per revolution) expected "
"to spin somewhat quickly (such as encoders being used in odometry pods) "
"should NOT be used on ports 1 and 2."
msgstr ""
"**IMPORTANTE: Sólo dos de los puertos de encoder (Puertos 0 y 3) pueden "
"seguir con precisión la posición/velocidad a altas velocidades**. Existen "
"dos métodos para conectar internamente un encoder al microprocesador de "
"Texas Instruments, a través de la interfaz de encoder en cuadratura (QEI) y "
"a través de temporizadores de propósito general (GPT). Los puertos 0 y 3 "
"utilizan el QEI integrado y son extremadamente precisos a altas velocidades,"
" mientras que los encoders que utilizan los GPTs a menudo empiezan a perder "
"recuentos a altas velocidades. Como resultado, los codificadores de alto "
"número de cuentas por revolución (CPR) (aquellos con más de 4000 cuentas por"
" revolución) que se espera que giren con cierta rapidez (como los "
"codificadores que se utilizan en los pods de odometría) NO deberían "
"utilizarse en los puertos 1 y 2."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:64
msgid "Two XT30 Connectors"
msgstr "Dos conectores XT30"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:66
msgid ""
"Care should be taken when moving around cables as these connectors have been"
" known to fail and break off the board."
msgstr ""
"Hay que tener cuidado al mover los cables, ya que se sabe que estos "
"conectores fallan y se desprenden de la placa."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:67
msgid ""
"In addition, XT30s will wear and get loose with time. See `XT30 Pins are "
"Compressed - Expansion Hub Troubleshooting "
"<https://docs.revrobotics.com/duo-control/troubleshooting-the-control-"
"system/expansion-hub-troubleshooting#xt30-pins-are-compressed>`_ for details"
" on the issue and how to fix it."
msgstr ""
"Además, los XT30 se desgastan y se aflojan con el tiempo. Consulte `XT30 "
"Pins are Compressed - Expansion Hub Troubleshooting "
"<https://docs.revrobotics.com/duo-control/troubleshooting-the-control-"
"system/expansion-hub-troubleshooting#xt30-pins-are-compressed>`_ para "
"obtener más detalles sobre el problema y cómo solucionarlo."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:68
msgid "USB Mini-B Connector"
msgstr "Conector USB Mini-B"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:70
msgid ""
"Uses the FTDI FT230XQ chip to bridge the internal UART to USB, allowing an "
"Expansion Hub to connect over USB to a Control Hub, Android device, "
"computer, or other such device. The FT230XQ is capable of USB Full Speed (12"
" Mbps) on the USB side and 3 MBaud on the UART side, and 5V output to charge"
" a phone. According to REV, the 5V output is not compatible with any of the "
"remaining Android phones still legal in FTC.  This USB chip is disabled by "
"the compute board of the Control Hub, meaning this port is not functional "
"out-of-the-box on a Control Hub."
msgstr ""
"Utiliza el chip FTDI FT230XQ para puentear la UART interna a USB, "
"permitiendo que el Expansion Hub se conecte a través de USB al Control Hub, "
"dispositivo Android, ordenador u otro dispositivo similar. El FT230XQ es "
"capaz de USB Full Speed (12 Mbps) en el lado USB y 3 MBaud en el lado UART, "
"y 5V de salida para cargar un teléfono. Según REV, la salida de 5V no es "
"compatible con ninguno de los teléfonos Android que aún son legales en la "
"FTC.  Este chip USB está deshabilitado por la placa de computación del "
"Control Hub, lo que significa que este puerto no es funcional fuera de la "
"caja en un Control Hub."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:71
msgid "Internal Connector"
msgstr "Conector interno"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:73
msgid ""
"This connector is what is used to connect to the compute daughterboard. It "
"has a UART connection, as well as power and ground. All Lynx modules that "
"came is part of an Control Hub will have this connector, but Lynx modules "
"sold as Expansion Hubs may or may not have this connector. A Lynx board from"
" an Expansion Hub that contains the connector, when connected with a Control"
" Hub's daughterboard, will work as a Control Hub. To go the other way, the "
"Hub address has to be changed to something other than the Control Hub "
"address of 173. You can change the address once the daughterboard is removed"
" by plugging it into an Android device running the Robot Controller app and "
"using the function in the settings to change the address. (Note that "
"connecting it to another Control Hub is unlikely to work, due to the address"
" interference betwen the two Lynx modules. The Driver Hub works fine for "
"this purpose, but make sure to uninstall the Robot Controller app from it "
"afterwards, so it doesn't potentially interfere with the Driver Station "
"app!)"
msgstr ""
"Este conector es el que se utiliza para conectarse a la placa hija de "
"computación. Tiene una conexión UART, así como alimentación y tierra. Todos "
"los módulos Lynx que vienen como parte de un Control Hub tendrán este "
"conector, pero los módulos Lynx vendidos como Expansion Hubs pueden o no "
"tener este conector. Una placa Lynx de un Expansion que contenga el "
"conector, cuando se conecte con una placa hija de un Control Hub, funcionará"
" como un Control Hub. Para ir en la otra dirección, la dirección del Hub "
"tiene que ser cambiada a otra que no sea la dirección del Control Hub de "
"173. Puedes cambiar la dirección una vez que hayas retirado la tarjeta "
"secundaria conectándola a un dispositivo Android que ejecute la aplicación "
"Robot Controller y utilizando la función en la configuración para cambiar la"
" dirección. (Tenga en cuenta que la conexión a otro concentrador de control "
"es poco probable que funcione, debido a la interferencia de dirección betwen"
" los dos módulos Lynx. El Driver Hub funciona bien para este propósito, pero"
" asegúrese de desinstalar la aplicación Robot Controller de él después, para"
" que no interfiera potencialmente con la aplicación Driver Station)."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:76
msgid "Control Hub"
msgstr "Control Hub"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:78
msgid ""
"The Control Hub is an Expansion Hub with an embedded single-board compute "
"daughterboard connected to it. This enables it to not need a separate Robot "
"Controller phone, as the compute board functions as the Robot Controller. "
"Internally, LynxCommands are sent over from the daughterboard to the Lynx "
"board over an internal UART connection."
msgstr ""
"El Control Hub es un Expansion Hub con una tarjeta hija de computación "
"integrada conectada a él. Esto le permite no necesitar un teléfono "
"Controlador de Robot separado, ya que la placa de cómputo funciona como el "
"Controlador de Robot. Internamente, los comandos Lynx se envían desde la "
"placa hija a la placa Lynx a través de una conexión UART interna."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:80
msgid ""
"The compute board is based on the `96Boards CE Specification, Version 1.0 "
"<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/96boards/documentation/master/Specifications/96Boards-"
"CE-Specification.pdf>`_, though it is unknown how many of the features of "
"the two expansion connectors are wired up/functional beyond the UART and "
"handful of GPIO lines used to connect to the Lynx board."
msgstr ""
"La placa de computación se basa en la `96Boards CE Specification, Version "
"1.0 "
"<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/96boards/documentation/master/Specifications/96Boards-"
"CE-Specification.pdf>`_, aunque se desconoce cuántas de las características "
"de los dos conectores de expansión están cableadas/funcionales más allá de "
"la UART y un puñado de líneas GPIO utilizadas para conectar con la placa "
"Lynx."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:83
msgid ""
"The original version of the Control Hub (REV-31-1152) actually used a "
"`Dragonboard 410c <https://www.96boards.org/product/dragonboard410c/>`_ as "
"the compute board.  This version of the Control Hub was never used in, nor "
"legal for, FTC; it appears to have only been used in early *FIRST*\\ |reg| "
"Global seasons."
msgstr ""
"La versión original del Control Hub (REV-31-1152) utilizaba en realidad una "
"`Dragonboard 410c <https://www.96boards.org/product/dragonboard410c/>`_ como"
" placa de cálculo.  Esta versión del Control Hub nunca se utilizó, ni fue "
"legal para FTC; parece que sólo se utilizó en las primeras temporadas de "
"*FIRST* |reg| Global."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:85
msgid ""
"The Control Hub compute board runs a customized version of Android 7.1. It "
"does not have a proper heatsink on the SOC, only an RF shield that does not "
"touch the SOC, which can cause thermal throttling when heavy processes such "
"as vision pipelines are used. A large amount of heat seems to be sunk by the"
" daughterboard PCB, which acts like a heat spreader."
msgstr ""
"La placa de cálculo Control Hub ejecuta una versión personalizada de Android"
" 7.1. No tiene un disipador térmico adecuado en el SOC, solo un escudo de RF"
" que no toca el SOC, lo que puede causar ahogo térmico cuando se usan "
"procesos pesados como los pipelines de visión. Una gran cantidad de calor "
"parece ser absorbida por la placa hija de PCB, que actúa como un disipador "
"de calor."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:87
msgid "SOC: Rockchip RK3328"
msgstr "SOC: Rockchip RK3328"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:89
msgid "CPU: Quad-core ARM\\ |reg| Cortex-A53"
msgstr "CPU: Quad-core ARM\\ |reg| Cortex-A53"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:91
msgid ""
"The device tree in `the official kernel "
"<https://github.com/REVrobotics/kernel-controlhub-android>`_ seems to "
"indicate that the CPU can clock up to 1.5 GHz"
msgstr ""
"El árbol de dispositivos en `el kernel oficial "
"<https://github.com/REVrobotics/kernel-controlhub-android>`_ parece indicar "
"que la CPU puede alcanzar hasta 1,5 GHz."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:92
msgid "GPU - ARM\\ |reg| Mali 450MP4"
msgstr "GPU - ARM |reg| Mali 450MP4"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:94
msgid "HDMI 2.0 support for 4k @ 60Hz"
msgstr "Compatible con HDMI 2.0 para 4k a 60 Hz"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:95
msgid "RAM: 1GB DDR3"
msgstr "RAM: 1 GB DDR3"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:96
msgid "Storage: 8 to 16GB of eMMC flash memory"
msgstr "Almacenamiento: de 8 a 16 GB de memoria flash eMMC"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:98
msgid ""
"\"8GB eMMC 4.51\" is the spec officially listed by REV, but multiple real-"
"world units that were checked all had 16GB eMMC chips found on their boards."
msgstr ""
"\"8GB eMMC 4.51\" es la especificación oficial de REV, pero varias unidades "
"reales que se comprobaron tenían chips eMMC de 16GB en sus placas."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:99
msgid ""
"According to REV, in a support email: **\"Original builds of the Control Hub"
" were manufactured with 8GB eMMC chips. However, some 16GB versions were "
"made due to supply chain constraints. Recent Control Hubs (purchased after "
"2022) are more likely to have the 16GB eMMC chip.\"**"
msgstr ""
"Según REV, en un correo electrónico de soporte: **\"Las versiones originales"
" del Control Hub se fabricaron con chips eMMC de 8 GB. Sin embargo, algunas "
"versiones de 16 GB se hicieron debido a las limitaciones de la cadena de "
"suministro. Es más probable que los Control Hubs recientes (comprados "
"después de 2022) tengan el chip eMMC de 16 GB \"**."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:100
msgid ""
"USB: 1x USB 3.0, 1x USB 2.0, 1x internal USB 2.0 used to connect the Wi-Fi "
"chip"
msgstr ""
"USB: 1x USB 3.0, 1x USB 2.0, 1x USB 2.0 interno utilizado para conectar el "
"chip Wi-Fi"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/software/adv-control-system/control-system-internals.rst:101
msgid "Wi-Fi: Realtek RTL8821CU"
msgstr "Wi-Fi: Realtek RTL8821CU"

